-- Apple Manager Devine Requests Jail Release as He Posts Bail
-- B y   J o e l   R o s e n b l a t t
-- 2010-09-21T23:52:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-21/apple-manager-accused-of-taking-kickbacks-posts-bail-to-get-out-of-jail.html
Paul Devine, the Apple Inc. manager
accused of taking kickbacks in exchange for company secrets,
will post a bond of $612,000 from his foreign bank accounts in a
bid to win release from prison, according to court documents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joel Rosenblatt in San Francisco at 
